data.title: Jacob Dean
data.text:
2015

• Appeared in four of UVa’s 15 games

• Saw time against Rutgers, VMI, Richmond and Penn

• Scored first collegiate goal at VMI

• Picked up three ground balls on the season

• Secured a career-high two ground balls against Richmond

• Recognized on ACC Academic Honor Roll

2014

• Appeared in one of UVa’s 16 games

• Made collegiate debut against VMI

• Picked up one ground ball against the Keydets

HIGH SCHOOL

• Finished high school career with 122 career goals as a three-year varsity starter

• Under Armour All-Star

• 2013 US Lacrosse All-American

• Co-Player of Year South Jersey 2013 – Philly Lacrosse

• 2013 first teamAll-South Jersey

• 2013 first team all-county and all-conference

• Shawnee Team MVP in 203

• Helped lead Shawnee to the South Jersey Group 3 Champions in 2013

• Scored 50 goals and had 20 assists

• Helped lead Shawnee to the Olympic Conference American Division Championship

• Outstanding Athlete Shawnee High School 2012-2013

• Outstanding Scholar-Athlete Shawnee High School 2012-2013

• Played football where he won the 2012 Burlington County Football Club Scholar Athlete Award

• 2012 West Jersey Football Scholar Athlete Award

• Was second team all-conference in football

• Was ranked No. 11 in his class of 387

• Member of the National Honor Society

• Member of the President’s Honor Roll

• National Latin Exam-Magna Cum Laude 2012

• National Latin Exam- Cum Laude 2011

• Honor Roll years 2009-2013

• Played high school lacrosse at same school as former UVa All-American Chris LaPierre
